When a small group of living things (small population) separates themselves from the main population from which they originate (for example, if they move through a mountain range or a river or if they move to a new island, or if they cannot easily return to a new island or a new island or a new island or a new island or a new island or a new island or a new island or a new island or a new island or a new island or a new island or a new island or
